{
  "texts": [
    "According to the authors, the CPA is possible due to a malicious client.",
    "As we have discussed in the first scenario, poison content is stored by all CS between the attacker and clients.",
    "So, the malicious content can be spread throughout the entire network due to multiple interests received for the same piece of content.",
    "C. Best Route Forwarding Scenario: In this scenario, the attacker sends a new interest again and again for the same piece of poison data to make this vulnerable to the DoS attack.",
    "The authors have pointed out that these attack scenarios have an immense influence on every NDN router."
  ]
}